<h1>Triangle Calculator</h1>

<h3>Instructions</h3>

<p>Enter values three of the six sides and angles of the triangle and the o=
ther three values will be computed.  The number of significant values enter=
ed will determine the number of significant figures in the results.</p>


<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

<div>
<b>Q:</b> I like your triangles, especially the ones that have interior ang=
les not summing to 180 degrees. Neat! Try sides equal to 1,2,2.
</div>
<div>
<b>A:</b> Because each of the sides you entered has so few significant figu=
res, the angles are all rounded to come out to 80, 80, and 30 (each with on=
e significant figure).
Entering sides of values 1.00, 2.00, and 2.00 will yield much more acurate =
results of 75.5, 75.5, and 29.0.
</div>

